data.name: RasterBinTool_Description
data.value: This bins the values of a raster so that there will be large regions of equal values. This will replace the raster value with the middle value of the bin range that it falls with. The baseValue represents the starting point of the first boundary, while the bin size represents the total distance between raster values. So for instance, an interval of every 20, starting at 10 would have a bin size of 20, and a base value of 10. The cells ranging from 10 to 30 would all get the half value of 20.
